Singleton Pattern
Database Connection Manager
Overview

This project implements a database connection manager using the Singleton design pattern. The Singleton pattern is a creational design pattern that ensures a class has only one instance and provides a global point of access to it. In this example, DatabaseConnectionManager ensures that only one instance of the connection manager exists.

Project Structure

The project consists of the following components:

DatabaseConnectionManager: The Singleton class that provides a global point of access to the database connection.
Main: A class to demonstrate the creation and usage of the DatabaseConnectionManager instance.
